{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770734454,"nonce":"M07eg0OSyQGvFpBs7fHoO7sGC6s=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87pwrV4","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/178","origin":"github"},"title":"Agent rules should require worktree isolation for feature branch work","message":"## Problem\n\nDuring a session addressing PR #177 review comments, the agent repeatedly attempted to `git checkout` and `cherry-pick` directly in the main repository checkout. This is unsafe in a multi-agent workspace where other agents may be using the main checkout concurrently. The user had to intervene twice to prevent it.\n\nThe agent also initially tried to create a worktree in `/tmp` rather than using the existing `worktree_create.sh` script.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`WORKFORCE_PROTOCOL.md` describes worktrees as \"Recommended\" (section 1 heading), but nothing in `AI_RULES.md` or the platform-specific instructions **requires** agents to:\n\n1. Use worktrees (not `git checkout`) when working on feature branches\n2. Use the existing `worktree_create.sh` / `worktree_enter.sh` scripts rather than ad-hoc worktree creation\n3. Never switch branches in the main checkout\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nAdd explicit rules to `AI_RULES.md` (and/or platform-specific instructions):\n\n- **NEVER run `git checkout \u003cbranch\u003e` in the main repository checkout** — use a worktree instead\n- **ALWAYS use `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh`** to create worktrees (not `git worktree add` directly)\n- **Use `.agent/scripts/worktree_enter.sh`** to enter existing worktrees\n\n## Related\n\n- #122 — Worktree naming scheme (different aspect of worktree workflow)\n- PR #177 — Session where this friction was encountered\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}